PrecisAmendment to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS SCHEDULE NO. 785 requiring that "peanut oil" be declared by its common name on food labels in order to increase information and product choice for consumers concerned with the allergenic potential of peanuts and the presence of any peanut products in foods, effective May 2, 1994.
